result.execSummary:
The defendant Ryan P. Murray was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Theft-Movable Property >$10,000-$100,000, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 1:25 PM /Room 301/ Defendant Ryan P. Murray in court, in custody at Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer in court for Ryan P. Murray.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin. Plea agreement. State requests on Ct. 1 Bail jumping - dismissed but read in, Ct. 2 Bail jumping -guilty or no contest, 2 yrs prison, 1 yr initial confinement, 1 yr extended sup, court costs, concurrent to one another and consecutive to all others, Ct. 3 guilty/or no contest Theft - guilty, 2 yrs prison, 1 yr initial confinement, 1 yr extended sup, court costs, concurrent, consecutive to ct. 2. Waiver previously filed. Court advises defendant of rights. Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing. Court finds defendant is voluntarily waiving right. Court finds probable cause and binds case over. Information filed. Def atty does not have, but waives acceptance and reading. Court reviews plea questionnaire with defendant. Defendant pleads no contest to ct 2. and ct 3. Court grants states motion to dismiss but read in ct 1. Court advises defendant of rights. Court reviews elements and penalties. Defendant enters pleas voluntarily. Court advises defendant of not being legal citizen. Defendant's atty is satisfied. Court finds defendant has entered freely into plea agreement. Court finds factual basis. Court accepts plea of no contest to ct. 2 and ct. 3. Court finds defendant guilty of ct. 2 bail jumping and ct 3. theft - movable property. Sentencing remarks by state. State has complied with victims rights. Sentencing remarks by defendant's atty. No remarks by defendant. Court reviews background of defendant. Court orders on Ct. 2 - bail jumping - 2 yrs prison, 1 yr initial confinement, 1 yr extended sup, court costs, $250 DNA surcharge and sample unless already provided, concurrent with one another, but consecutive to any other sentence already ordered. Ct. 3 - theft - 2 yrs prison, 1 yr initial confinement, 1 yr extended sup, court costs, concurrent with one another, but consecutive to any other sentence already ordered. Court advises defendant of fire arm restrictions, voting rights,  not eligible for challenge incarceration, eligible for substance abuse program, 0 credit. Court advises defendant of post conviction rights. Court adjourned.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 7, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
No contact with victims or their business or residence

01:54 PM Defendant Ryan P. Murray in court with attorney Christopher Michael Restemayer.  Defendant Ryan P. Murray in custody.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Ryan P. Murray appeared by video means with Attorney.  All parties via zoom. State ask to quash warrant and set bond.  Court quash warrant. Atty Restemayer has copy of complaint, waives reading, reserve rights and ask bond to be set.  State heard on bail/bond $2,000 cash, no contact with victims or their business or residence. Atty Restemayer doesn't object. Cout will go over waiver of p.h. form. State advise plea & sentencing already set.  Court orders $2,000 cash bond with above condition.  Atty Restemayer waives time limits for p.h.  Def. waives time limts for ph. Court accepts waiver of time limits for p.h.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 7, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
